== Prep the ingredients ==

Halve, peel, and finely chop the @Yellow Onion{1%unit}. Mince or grate the @Garlic{2%clove}.

Core, seed and remove the white ribs from the @Red Bell Pepper{2%unit}(cored, seeded, rib removed), then thinly slice.

Drain and rinse the @Black Beans{26.8%ounce}.

Thinly slice the @Romaine Lettuce{2%unit}(thinly sliced).

Juice the @Lime{2%unit}(juiced).

== Cook the vegetables ==

Heat a large drizzle of @Olive Oil{2%tablespoon} in a large #pan{} over medium heat.

Add the onion and garlic and cook for ~{4-5%minutes}, until softened.

Add the bell pepper and cook for ~{5-6%minutes}, until softened. Season with @salt{box} and @pepper{box}.

== Mash the beans ==

While the veggies cook, coarsely mash the black beans in a #bowl{} using a #fork{}. Add the mashed beans to the pan with the vegetables and cook for another ~{1-2%minutes}, until heated though. Season with salt and pepper.

== Assemble the quesadillas ==

Heat a large pan over medium heat. Place one @Flour Tortilla{8%unit} in the pan and sprinkle one side with ¼ the @Mozzarella Cheese{16%ounce}. Top with half of the bean mixture and another ¼ of the cheese. Fold the tortilla over to form a half moon and cook for ~{2-3%minutes} on the first side, until golden brown. Flip and cook on the other side for ~{2-3%minutes}, until melted and golden brown. Repeat for the remaining quesadillas.

> To keep the finished quesadillas warm, place them on a #baking sheet{} in a 200 degree oven until the rest are done.

== Make the dressing and salad ==

In a large bowl, combine @Honey{1%ounce}, the lime juice, and a large drizzle of olive oil. Season with salt and pepper. Toss the lettuce and @Grape Tomatoes{8%ounce} into the bowl with the dressing and season with salt and pepper.

== Plate ==

Cut the quesadillas into wedges and serve with the romaine salad and a dollop of @Sour Cream{2%ounce} for dipping. Enjoy!